<div class="xar-mod-head"><span class="xar-mod-title"><xar:mlstring>Administration - Smilies</xar:mlstring></span></div>
<div class="xar-mod-body">
    <xar:template type="module" module="smilies" file="admin-menu" />
    <h2><xar:mlstring>Overview</xar:mlstring></h2>
      <img src="#xarTplGetImage('admin_generic.gif','base')#" class="xar-module-icon" alt="official icon" width="96" height="96" />
        <h2>
            <xar:mlstring>What is it?</xar:mlstring>
        </h2>
        <p>
            <em><xar:mlstring>Smilies is an utility module</xar:mlstring></em>
            <xar:mlstring>It is currently responsible for accomplishing these tasks:</xar:mlstring>
            <xar:mlstring>The Smilies module will transform text that is using smilies code to images.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
        <h2>
            <xar:mlstring>How to use it?</xar:mlstring>
        </h2>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>
            From the menu, you have three choices.  "Add Smilies", "View Smiles", and "Modify Config".
            </xar:mlstring>
        </p>
        <ol>
            <li><xar:mlstring><strong>Add Smilie</strong> -- Allows you to add new smilies to your system.</xar:mlstring></li>
            <li><xar:mlstring><strong>Manage Smilies</strong> -- Allows you to view the smilies that you have configured on your system.</xar:mlstring></li>
            <li><xar:mlstring><strong>Modify Config</strong> -- Allows you to change some of the key settings controlling the behaviour of the module</xar:mlstring>
              <ul>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Specify the number of smilies to display per page</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>
                    Specify HTML tags to ignore when transforming smiley code, useful for, eg, the bbcode [code] tags
                  </xar:mlstring>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>Accepts a comma delimited list of lowercase valid HTML tags.</xar:mlstring>
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li><xar:mlstring>Optionally display all codes for each emotion on user main</xar:mlstring></li>
                <li>
                  <xar:mlstring>Optionally specify a folder containing images to use for smilies</xar:mlstring>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>Folder must exist in one of the following folders (if the folder doesn't exist, or you leave this option empty, images will be served from these folders):</xar:mlstring>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>In the module itself </xar:mlstring>
                  <code>/modules/smilies/xarimages/</code>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>Or when over-ridden by the theme in </xar:mlstring>
                  <code>/themes/{current-theme-dir}/modules/smilies/images/</code>
                  </p>
                  <p>
                  <xar:mlstring>Images must be named according to the Icon Path specified for each smilie configured on your system</xar:mlstring>
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </li>
        </ol>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Blocks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <ul>
            <li><xar:mlstring>smilies</xar:mlstring></li>
        </ul>
        <h3>
            <xar:mlstring>Included Hooks</xar:mlstring>
        </h3>
        <p>
            <xar:mlstring>The Smilies Transform Hook can be used on any content module that calls transforms.</xar:mlstring>
        </p>
  <h3>
    <xar:mlstring>Further Information</xar:mlstring>
  </h3>
  <p>
    <xar:mlstring>Further information on the Smilies module can be found at</xar:mlstring>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Smilies Extension page at</xar:mlstring> <a title="#xarML('Smilies Module - Xaraya Extension 153')#" href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/release/153.html">Xaraya Extension and Releases</a>.
      <xar:mlstring> Click on Version History tab at the bottom to get the latest release information.</xar:mlstring>
    </li>
    <li><xar:mlstring>Related tutorials and documentation on Smilies found at</xar:mlstring> <a href="http://www.xaraya.com/index.php/keywords/smilies/" title="#xarML('Related documentation on Smilies')#"><xar:mlstring>Xaraya Documentation.</xar:mlstring></a>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="xar-sub">
    <strong>&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Smilies Module Overview</xar:mlstring></strong><br />&nbsp;<xar:mlstring>Version</xar:mlstring> 1.0.3-RC1&nbsp; 2008-09-25
  </p>

  <h3><xar:mlstring>Current Smilies</xar:mlstring></h3>
  <xar:if condition="!empty($icons)">
     <ul>
        <xar:loop name="$icons">
            <li>
                <img src="#xarTplGetImage($loop:key, 'smilies')#" />
                <strong>#xarVarPrepForDisplay($loop:item['0']['emotion'])#</strong>
                <ul>
                    <xar:loop name="$loop:item">
                        <li><strong style="width: 10em;">#xarVarPrepForDisplay($loop:item.code)#</strong> <xar:comment>#xarVarPrepForDisplay($loop:item.emotion)#</xar:comment></li>
                    </xar:loop>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </xar:loop>
     </ul>
  <xar:else />
      <p><xar:mlstring>None</xar:mlstring></p>
  </xar:if>

</div>
